WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.680
Hi, I'm Dr. Paul Chin.

00:00:02.160 --> 00:00:05.880
Welcome to AI Reverse Engineering with OpenClaw and MCP.

00:00:06.740 --> 00:00:08.500
Reverse engineering is changing.

00:00:09.120 --> 00:00:12.260
For decades, reverse engineers have relied on powerful tools

00:00:12.260 --> 00:00:15.400
such as debuggers, disassemblers, and decompilers.

00:00:16.100 --> 00:00:18.380
But no matter how advanced the tools became,

00:00:18.920 --> 00:00:21.660
the analysts still had to perform most of the work manually.

00:00:22.620 --> 00:00:24.640
Today, a new approach is emerging.

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:27.200
By combining large language models,

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:30.700
the Model Context Protocol or MCP and OpenCLAW,

00:00:31.080 --> 00:00:36.360
we can create AI-powered workflows where intelligent agents interact directly with reverse engineering tools

00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:38.960
and help automate complex analysis tasks.

00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:43.660
In this course, you'll learn how to connect AI to real reverse engineering tools,

00:00:44.200 --> 00:00:48.300
enabling it to inspect binaries, gather information, analyze results,

00:00:48.600 --> 00:00:50.760
and assist you throughout the reversing process.

00:00:51.180 --> 00:00:55.340
This is much more than simply asking ChatGPT to explain assembly code.

00:00:55.340 --> 00:01:01.700
You learn how OpenCLAW acts as the orchestrator, how MCP acts as the bridge between AI and tools,

00:01:02.100 --> 00:01:06.580
and how multiple tools can work together as part of a coordinated reverse engineering workflow.

00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:12.200
Whether you're a reverse engineer, malware analyst, ethical hacker, penetration tester,

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:15.480
or simply curious about the future of AI-driven cybersecurity,

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:20.280
this course will give you a practical introduction to the next generation of reverse engineering.

00:01:20.860 --> 00:01:22.860
AI is no longer just a helper.

00:01:22.860 --> 00:01:28.060
It can become a collaborator, a tool operator, and a workflow orchestrator.

00:01:29.060 --> 00:01:30.220
What you will learn.

00:01:30.220 --> 00:01:36.180
What is Model Context Protocol, MCP, and how it connects AI to tools.

00:01:36.600 --> 00:01:39.440
What is OpenClaw and how it enables multi-tool workflows.

00:01:39.960 --> 00:01:42.040
How AI agents remember workflows.

00:01:42.680 --> 00:01:46.420
Connecting AI to debuggers, prompt engineering for binary analysis.

00:01:46.960 --> 00:01:49.380
How to easily fix OpenClaw issues.

00:01:49.900 --> 00:01:51.460
Managing different AI models.

00:01:51.460 --> 00:01:56.820
Using Codex and Claude code with OpenClaw. Dynamic and static analysis.

00:01:56.820 --> 00:02:02.680
Connecting OpenClaw to x64DBG, Ghidra and dnSpy using MCP.

00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:07.180
Using OpenClaw to interpret assembly code to derive serial key.

00:02:07.180 --> 00:02:12.940
Using OpenClaw to create keygens, bypass trial period, disable nags, and more.

00:02:12.940 --> 00:02:18.620
Who this course is for. Reverse engineers who want to increase

00:02:18.620 --> 00:02:24.380
their productivity by using AI,  malware analysts looking to automate workflows, ethical hackers

00:02:24.380 --> 00:02:30.060
and pen testers exploring AI driven tooling. Team developers curious about multi-tooling ai systems.

00:02:30.780 --> 00:02:34.860
Anyone interested in AI plus cyber security integration using open claw.

00:02:36.460 --> 00:02:42.540
Prerequisites. Familiarity with tools like debuggers or disassemblers helpful - not required.

00:02:42.540 --> 00:02:47.540
No prior AI experience needed, you'll learn everything step by step.

00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:53.980
Windows PC running Windows 11 in Oracle VirtualBox.

00:02:53.980 --> 00:03:01.980
My background. I am a semi-retired college lecturer and cybersecurity industry trainer with PhD in computer science.

00:03:01.980 --> 00:03:05.980
I have more than 30 years experience teaching computer science and IT.

00:03:05.980 --> 00:03:08.980
I welcome you to this course and I'll see you inside.

